NEWS for xfprint
================

4.5.90
======
- Make settings-dialogs use xfconf instead of mcs-manager
- Make settings-dialogs independent apps instead of mcs-plugins
- Fix segfault when there is no default printer selected in backend
  (bug #3816)
- Update Arabic, Greek, Galician, Brazilian Portuguese, Latvian and 
  Sinhala translations


4.4.0
=====
- Prevent xfprint4 from removing the printed file when the filters aren't
  applied
- Fix incompatibility with CUPS 1.2 (bug #2107)
- Remove pointless warning messages
- Use themable 'printer' icon
- Add shortcuts in printer queue dialog

4.3.90.2
========
- Use GtkIconTheme instead of deprecated XfceIconTheme

4.3.90.1
========
- Remove the a2ps dependency now it looks for it at runtime
- New printing backend framework using GtkUIManager in order to simplify GUI modifications
- Show the printer state in the printer list dialog (only supported by CUPS backend)

4.2.3
=====
- Get the cups server address from CUPS config (fix #918)
- Add support for CUPS instances (fix #1096)
- Update some copyright notices
- Updated af, ca, fi, he, ja, ko, lt translations
- Added el, ku translations

4.2.2
=====
- FILE plugin removal from 4.2.1 doesn't make xfprint crash anymore
- French docs added
- Add 'None' as a choice in the printing system selection dialog (fix #879)
- Add support for printcap aliases in BSD-LPR backend (fix #821)
- Fix LDFLAGS to avoid problem when loading backend plugin (fix #871)

4.2.1
=====
- Remove FILE backend and add a print-to-file entry in the printing dialog
- Multiple fixes in the BSD-LPR backend (thanks to Jason Keltz for pointing them out)

4.2.0
=====
- Fix problem with locating printing-system modules when installing in a different prefix (Jasper)

4.1.99.3 (4.2 RC3)
==================
- Fix display of jobs for CUPS backend (Jean-François)

- Add queueing support for bsd-lpr backend (Jean-François)

- Several translation updates (Jean-François)

4.1.99.2 (4.2 RC2)
==================

4.1.99.1 (4.2 RC1)
==================

4.1.91 (4.2 BETA2)
==================
- Several translation updates (Jean-François)

- Fix empty printer list freeze with CUPS (Jean-François)

- Fix MCS-plugin window closing (Edscott)


4.1.90 (4.2 BETA1)
==================
- Use gmodule as printing back-end (File, CUPS and BDR-LPR available so far) (Jean-François)
